format_1_answer_1.question:
If $\angle ABC$ is a straight angle, give the number of degrees in the measure of $\angle ABD$. [asy] pair A,B,C,D; A = dir(180); D = dir(60); C = dir(0);
draw(B--1.2*A,EndArrow); draw(B--1.2*D,EndArrow); label("A",A,S); dot(A);
label("B",B,S); draw(B--1.2*C,EndArrow); label("C",C,S); label("D",D,dir(135));
label("$6x^{\circ}$",B,NW); label("$3x^{\circ}$",B+.1,NE); dot(D); dot(C);
[/asy]

format_1_answer_0.question:
On a protractor, ray $BA$ goes through the 85-degree mark and ray $BC$ goes through the 30-degree mark. What is the measure, in degrees, of angle $ABC$?

[asy]
draw((0,0)--(2,0)..(1,1)..(0,0)..cycle,linewidth(2));

draw((1,0)--1.4dir(30)+(1,0),Arrow);
draw((1,0)--1.3dir(85)+(1,0),Arrow);

dot(1.1dir(85)+(1,0));
dot(1.2dir(30)+(1,0));

label("A",1.1dir(85)+(1,0),NW);
label("B",(1,0),S);
label("C",1.2dir(30)+(1,0),SE);

label("85",.9dir(85)+(1,0));
label("30",.9dir(30)+(1,0));

[/asy]
